There&#039;s always been intrigue and adventure at the heart of Calexico. Joey 
Burns and John Convertino have constantly imbued their music with an 
unparalleled sense of drama, calling upon the myths and iconography of the 
American West and its Spanish speaking neighbor Mexico. "Carried To Dust" 
represents the pinnacle of their achievement, a thrilling and moving journey 
through a landscape that draws upon the modern world as much as it does 
the decayed reminders of times past, stumbling upon unexpected delights 
whilst always moving forward with a pioneering sense of purpose.
